## Token Savings Rule
When reading files or web content for parsing, extraction, summarization, or pattern searching (not for code
reasoning/editing), delegate to `freeloader` via Bash instead of using Read/Grep/WebFetch. This applies even
mid-task (debugging, troubleshooting, etc.). For web content, pipe curl into freeloader:
`curl -s '<url>' | freeloader '<instructions>'`. Examples: searching logs for errors, extracting fields from
configs, summarizing API responses, finding patterns in data files, fetching and summarizing web pages.
Only use Read/Grep directly when you need to reason about code structure or make edits.
